body:
@miaofengwei Note that you can already easily create variable aliases w/o alias declarations: a package can be imported multiple times under different names ( example: https://play.golang.org/p/qeaGvLI1Dr ). Yet people don't do this in general.

We can also play with further restrictions (for instance, we can disallow the use of a qualified name if an alias has been defined for it in a package).

Many concerns about misuse have been brought up in this thread; but we really don't know how much misuse we're going to see in practice without getting some experience with the feature. I believe unintentional misuse will be insignificant. Especially with all the restrictions we are planning to put in place.
